title: World Of Tomorrow
description: World of Tomorrow Sound Effects Pack is an all-encompassing collection of audio elements designed to enhance your project's sonic landscape
longDescription:
With 20 whooshes, 20 impacts, 20 mechanical movement elements, 4 engine motor sound effects, 16 UI (User Interface), and 20 ambiences room tones textures, this pack contains a very useful selection of sound elements perfect to create a futuristic and dystopian soundscape.


Preview; https://youtu.be/F1NeleVvd2U
technicalDetails:
Features


  •  20 Whooshes to add motion and movement to your project. These are ideal for creating movement effects for objects and characters within your sci-fi or dystopian world.
  •  20 Impacts perfect for adding weight and impact to your project's sound design. Heavy hits, explosions, and other impactful sounds that will make your project's sound design stand out.
  •  20 Mechanical movement elements that can be used to create futuristic machines and technology sounds, from gears turning to robotic movement effects. These are ideal for creating a sci-fi or dystopian atmosphere with advanced technology.
  • 4 Engine motor sound effects to create futuristic vehicle sounds, from spacecraft to advanced ground vehicles. These are perfect for creating a dynamic atmosphere within your sci-fi or dystopian project.
  • 16 UI (User Interface) sounds that can be used for the user interface of advanced technology. These sounds include notifications, buttons, and other sounds that add depth and realism to your project.
  • 20 Ambiences room tones textures that can be used to create a soundscape that evokes a specific mood or atmosphere, such as futuristic interiors or a dystopian wasteland. These sounds will help you create a world that feels alive and immersive.


Number of Audio Waves: 100

Number of Audio Cues: 100

Sample rate / bit rate: 24bits 96KHz

Do Sound FX loop: Ambiences, Room Tones and Engines loop seamlessly.

Minutes of audio provided: 17:00

Supported Development Platforms:

Windows: Yes

Mac: Yes
